node.text:
The journey of conception, all the way through to birth, is like training wheels for becoming a mother. It prepares you for what you need to embrace as a parent—surrender.

There is a spiritual way to travel the path to parenthood that is backed with faith and miracles. Take it from me, I know how hard this journey can be. But today I’m here to remind you of the miracles. I’ve been there. It took me three years to conceive my son. I spent 2020 in and out of the fertility clinic doing IVF for a second child. I experienced postpartum depression that rocked me to my core. But no matter how hard the journey has been for me, there was light on the other side. If it weren’t for my spiritual faith and commitment to surrender, I wouldn’t be able to share this episode with you today. 

May this prayer open you up to the radical acceptance that being a mother is a transformational practice of surrender.

Take a moment, take a deep breath in, and pray with me. 

This week's episode of Dear Gabby is dedicated to The Spiritual Path to Becoming a Mother! 🎙Check out the episode now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link! 🔗 in bio @gabbybernstein

Whether you’re a parent who’s suffered a miscarriage, someone who’s made the difficult choice to abort, or a person struggling with conception, this episode will offer you hope. My intention for this episode is to remind you that when you surrender, the Universe reveals a parenting path far beyond what you could have imagined.

There is a spiritual way to travel this path that is backed with faith and miracles. Take it from me, I know how hard this journey can be. But today I’m here to remind you of the miracles. I’ve been there. It took me three years to conceive my son. I spent 2020 in and out of the fertility clinic doing IVF for a second child. I experienced postpartum depression that rocked me to my core. But no matter how hard the journey has been for me, there was light on the other side. If it weren’t for my spiritual faith and commitment to surrender, I wouldn’t be able to share this episode with you today. 

🎙Check out episode #18, The Spiritual Path to Becoming a Mother, now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link in bio @gabbybernstein

Repeat after me: NO is the most loving response…

On episode #17 of the podcast I teach one of the best ways to break the pattern of doing things for others when it’s at your own expense. 

It’s called the No Game. And it’s great for when you’re feeling burned out.

Once a day, practice saying No. 

You’ll say:
🚫 "No, I’m not going to be able to help you with that." 
🚫 "No, I can’t do that for you."
🚫 "No, I’m not going to do whatever you need me to do."

Practice your No for 90 days. And keep going longer until repeating this new behavior becomes a habit. On the podcast, I break it down further. 

Listen now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link! 🔗 in bio @gabbybernstein

node.text:
The journey of conception, all the way through to birth, is like training wheels for becoming a mother. It prepares you for what you need to embrace as a parent—surrender.

There is a spiritual way to travel the path to parenthood that is backed with faith and miracles. Take it from me, I know how hard this journey can be. But today I’m here to remind you of the miracles. I’ve been there. It took me three years to conceive my son. I spent 2020 in and out of the fertility clinic doing IVF for a second child. I experienced postpartum depression that rocked me to my core. But no matter how hard the journey has been for me, there was light on the other side. If it weren’t for my spiritual faith and commitment to surrender, I wouldn’t be able to share this episode with you today. 

May this prayer open you up to the radical acceptance that being a mother is a transformational practice of surrender.

Take a moment, take a deep breath in, and pray with me. 

This week's episode of Dear Gabby is dedicated to The Spiritual Path to Becoming a Mother! 🎙Check out the episode now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link! 🔗 in bio @gabbybernstein
